Your ablility for your service ti remain available by ensuring there is 
* no single point of failure and/ or ensure a certain level of performance 

Running your workload across multiple Availability Zones ensures that if 1 or 2 
AZs become unavailable your service /application remains available. 

Azure Load Balancer 
A load balancer allows you to evenly distribute traffic to multiple servers in one 
or datacenter. if a datacenter or server become unavailable (unhealthy) the load balancer will route 
the traffic to only available datacenters with servers 
